The other replies kind of hit on this, but I&#x27;ll expand on it by saying:<p>The collection creation methods existed because Java <i>could</i> perform type inference on methods but <i>could not</i> on constructors:<p><pre><code>  // Java 1.5
  Map<String,Integer> map = new HashMap<String,Integer>();
  // Guava
  Map<String,Integer> map = Maps.newHashMap();
  // Java 1.8 diamond notation
  Map<String,Integer> map = new HashMap<>();</code></pre>
